title: Justin Bieber shares video of Robbie Keane and Ireland celebrating their win over Germany
text:
Justin Bieber shares video of Robbie Keane and Ireland celebrating their win over Germany Justin Bieber shares video of Robbie Keane and Ireland celebrating their win over Germany Share 
So, it turns out Justin Bieber and Robbie Keane are friends. 
We know this because Keane sent the Biebs a video of Ireland celebrating on the team bus after their win over Germany, listening to the Canadian singer’s track What Do You Mean? Love to my brother Keano and the Irish squad on a big win today. Got this vid of them listening to #WhatDoYouMean after the win. Love it. 
— Justin Bieber (@justinbieber) October 9, 2015 Here it is. Robbie Keane and the Irish lads listening to #WhatDoYouMean after the victory pic.twitter.com/SsrWOKconw 
— Justin Bieber (@justinbieber) October 9, 2015 
Yep, that one really seems to have got the party started. 
Bieber’s a big football fan and has trained with Barcelona and Chelsea. Apparently he’s got a decent tackle on him. 
But somehow the idea that he’s chummy with former Coventry striker Keane just doesn’t seem quite right, even if the Ireland captain does now ply his trade in the glamorous surroundings of the Los Angeles Galaxy. 
Keane was an unused substitute as Ireland beat world champions Germany 1-0 to give themselves a great chance of reaching Euro 2016. (Brian Lawless/PA) 
Among Keane’s other musical chums are One Direction’s Niall Horan and Morrissey. Yes – that Morrissey, who is in fact related to the Ireland striker. 
We can’t see him being a big Bieber fan, somehow. My decision to wake up was just justified by learning that Robbie Keane is a cousin of Morrissey. My head hurts. pic.twitter.com/ndc3jhetnJ Share article 
— Thomas Hobbs (@thobbsjourno) August 21, 2015 Promoted Stories
